criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  diagnosis of Parkinson's disease according to the United Kingdom Brain Bank criteria;

          -  in stage 2-3 of the disease evolution according to the Hoehn and Yahr;

          -  treated with levodopa or its synergists;

          -  capable to walk independently indoors without aid;

          -  score above 15 point at UPDRS.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  presence of other neurological (excluding PD), orthopedic or cardiopulmonary
             problems;

          -  visual and auditory deficiency uncorrected;

          -  cognitive impairment that unable the subject to follow verbal instructions [assessed
             by the Montreal Cognitive Assessment (MoCA);

          -  score below 10 points in the Revised Movement Imagery Questionnaire.
